Doc Spatz,<br><br>
As I said somewhere up here not too long ago, all the world's a stage, especially this site. <br><br>
I just want you to understand that I have taken great care to examine my feelings about your behavior. Several trusted and professional individuals validate my feelings. It is good to know that I was not hallucinating how, what, and why I feel as I do. I expect that my feelings will continue because I have confidence that you will produce nothing of substance to change them. <br><br>
I have a memory. I recall in vivid detail the projectile vomiting of bigotry and hatred you call emotions, and the dramatic transformations into something soft and benign as if what had gone before did not happen or had no meaning.<br>
The violins playing the tune of &quot;open up to me&quot; and bare all was particularly unimaginative but predictable. Your assumption that everyone would go along with this baroque fuge of punishment and reward for forgetting your behavior is mistaken. Of course, we start it all over again, as soon as the crowd changes.<br><br>
Regardless of what you think or do not think of your actions, it is you who are accountable for them. Today, I find your behavior as unacceptable as I found it yesterday. It is with reasonable certainty that I will think similarly tomorrow.<br><br>
If you find this too esoteric for your tastes, or beyond your comprehension, too bad. <br><br>
You are still accountable for your unacceptable behavior.     
<p><code>--   (arthur varanelli) </code><p>


